cs.LO, cs.DB, cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with computational complexity and logic, specifically the complexity of constraint satisfaction problems (CSPs) and the expressiveness of Datalog programs. Therefore, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions relational structures and databases, which suggests cs.DB (Databases) as another likely sub-category. The use of permutation groups and the mention of graph isomorphism in the paper suggest cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as a possible sub-category. The paper also deals with algorithms and data structures, which could place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the mention of linear Datalog programs and their expressiveness suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as a possible sub-category.
